30// Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
31// BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
32// the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
33// static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
34// BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
35#if defined(BUILDING_V8_SHARED) && defined(USING_V8_SHARED)
36#error both BUILDING_V8_SHARED and USING_V8_SHARED are set - please check the\
37 build configuration to ensure that at most one of these is set
38#endif

42#elif USING_V8_SHARED
43# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
44#else
45# define V8_EXPORT
46#endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
47
48#else // V8_OS_WIN

53# define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
54# else
55# define V8_EXPORT
56# endif
57#else

215template <class T> class Handle {
216 public:
220 V8_INLINE Handle() : val_(0) {}
221
232 template <class S> V8_INLINE Handle(Handle<S> that)
233 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
239 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
240 }
241
245 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
246
250 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
251
252 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
253
254 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
255
262 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Handle<S>& that) const {
263 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
264 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
265 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
266 if (b == 0) return false;
267 return *a == *b;
268 }
269
270 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
271 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
272 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
273 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
274 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
275 if (b == 0) return false;
276 return *a == *b;
277 }
278
285 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Handle<S>& that) const {
286 return !operator==(that);
287 }
288
289 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
290 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
291 return !operator==(that);
292 }
293
294 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Handle<T> Cast(Handle<S> that) {
295#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
296 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
297 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
298 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Handle<T>();
299#endif
300 return Handle<T>(T::Cast(*that));
301 }
302
303 template <class S> V8_INLINE Handle<S> As() {
304 return Handle<S>::Cast(*this);
305 }
306
307 V8_INLINE static Handle<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Handle<T> that) {
308 return New(isolate, that.val_);
309 }
310 V8_INLINE static Handle<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
311 const PersistentBase<T>& that) {
312 return New(isolate, that.val_);
313 }
314
315 private:
316 friend class Utils;
317 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
318 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
319 template<class F> friend class Handle;
320 template<class F> friend class Local;
321 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
322 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
323 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
324 friend Handle<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
325 friend Handle<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
326 friend Handle<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
327 friend Handle<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
328 friend class Context;
329 friend class HandleScope;
330 friend class Object;
331 friend class Private;
332
336 V8_INLINE explicit Handle(T* val) : val_(val) {}
337
338 V8_INLINE static Handle<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
339
340 T* val_;
341};

414// Eternal handles are set-once handles that live for the life of the isolate.
415template <class T> class Eternal {
416 public:
417 V8_INLINE Eternal() : index_(kInitialValue) { }
418 template<class S>
419 V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : index_(kInitialValue) {
420 Set(isolate, handle);
421 }
422 // Can only be safely called if already set.
423 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate);
424 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() { return index_ == kInitialValue; }
425 template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
426
427 private:
428 static const int kInitialValue = -1;
429 int index_;
430};

563 // Phantom persistents work like weak persistents, except that the pointer to
564 // the object being collected is not available in the finalization callback.
565 // This enables the garbage collector to collect the object and any objects
566 // it references transitively in one GC cycle. At the moment you can either
567 // specify a parameter for the callback or the location of two internal
568 // fields in the dying object.

691template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
692 public:
696 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
702 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Handle<S> that)
703 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
704 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
705 }
711 template <class S, class M2>
712 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
713 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
714 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
715 }
722 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
723 Copy(that);
724 }
725 template <class S, class M2>
726 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
727 Copy(that);
728 }
729 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
730 Copy(that);
731 return *this;
732 }
733 template <class S, class M2>
734 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
735 Copy(that);
736 return *this;
737 }
743 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
744 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
745 }
746
747 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
748 template <class S>
749 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
750#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
751 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
752 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
753 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
754#endif
755 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(that);
756 }
757
758 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
759 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() { // NOLINT
760 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
761 }
762
763 private:
764 friend class Isolate;
765 friend class Utils;
766 template<class F> friend class Handle;
767 template<class F> friend class Local;
768 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
769 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
770
771 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent(S* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) { }
772 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
773 template<class S, class M2>
774 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
775};

4565struct JitCodeEvent {
4566 enum EventType {
4567 CODE_ADDED,
4568 CODE_MOVED,
4569 CODE_REMOVED,
4570 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
4571 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
4572 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
4573 };
4574 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
4575 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
4576 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
4577 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
4578 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
4579 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
4580
4581 // Type of event.
4582 EventType type;
4583 // Start of the instructions.
4584 void* code_start;
4585 // Size of the instructions.
4586 size_t code_len;
4587 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
4588 Handle<UnboundScript> script;
4589 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
4590 // code line information which is returned from the
4591 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
4592 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
4593 void* user_data;
4594
4595 struct name_t {
4596 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
4597 // zero-terminated.
4598 const char* str;
4599 // Number of chars in str.
4600 size_t len;
4601 };
4602
4603 struct line_info_t {
4604 // PC offset
4605 size_t offset;
4606 // Code postion
4607 size_t pos;
4608 // The position type.
4609 PositionType position_type;
4610 };
4611
4612 union {
4613 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
4614 struct name_t name;
4615
4616 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
4617 struct line_info_t line_info;
4618
4619 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
4620 void* new_code_start;
4621 };
4622};

6173const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
6174const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
6175const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
6176
6177// Tag information for HeapObject.
6178const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
6179const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
6180const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
6181
6182// Tag information for Smi.
6183const int kSmiTag = 0;
6184const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
6185const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
6186
6187template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
6188
6189template<int kSmiShiftSize>
6190V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6191 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6192 uintptr_t tagged_value =
6193 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
6194 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
6195}
6196
6197// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
6198template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
6199 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
6200 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
6201 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
6202 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
6203 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6204 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
6205 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
6206 }
6207 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6208 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
6209 }
6210 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
6211 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
6212 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
6213 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
6214 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
6215 //
6216 // CAUTION: The original code below:
6217 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
6218 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
6219 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
6220 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
6221 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
6222 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
6223 }
6224};
6225
6226// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
6227template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
6228 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
6229 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
6230 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
6231 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
6232 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6233 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
6234 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
6235 }
6236 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6237 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
6238 }
6239 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
6240 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
6241 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
6242 }
6243};
6244
6245typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
6246const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
6247const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
6248V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
6249V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

6407 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
6408 typedef internal::Object O;
6409 typedef internal::Internals I;
6410 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
6411 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
6412 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
6413 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
6414 int value_offset =
6415 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
6416 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
6417 }

6483void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
6484 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
6485 this->Reset();
6486 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;

6488 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
6489 M::Copy(that, this);

6502template <class T>
6503bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
6504 typedef internal::Internals I;
6505 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
6506 uint8_t node_state =
6507 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
6508 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
6509 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;

6684template<typename T>
6685void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
6686 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
6687 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
6688 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
6689 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
6690 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
6691 return;
6692 }
6693 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));

6878
6879Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
6880#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
6881 typedef internal::Object O;
6882 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
6883 typedef internal::Internals I;
6884 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
6885 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
6886 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
6887 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
6888 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
6889 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
6890 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
6891 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
6892 }
6893#endif
6894 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
6895}
6896
6897
6898void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
6899#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
6900 typedef internal::Object O;
6901 typedef internal::Internals I;
6902 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
6903 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
6904 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
6905 if (V8_LIKELY(I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType)) {
6906 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
6907 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
6908 }
6909#endif
6910 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
6911}

6930
6931String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
6932 typedef internal::Object O;
6933 typedef internal::Internals I;
6934 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
6935 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
6936 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
6937 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
6938 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
6939 } else {
6940 result = NULL;
6941 }
6942#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
6943 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
6944#endif
6945 return result;
6946}
6947
6948
6949String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
6950 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
6951 typedef internal::Object O;
6952 typedef internal::Internals I;
6953 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
6954 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
6955 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
6956 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
6957 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
6958 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
6959 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
6960 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
6961 }
6962#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
6963 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
6964#endif
6965 return resource;
6966}

7380
7381int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
7382 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
7383 typedef internal::Internals I;
7384 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
7385 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
7386 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
7387 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
7388 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
7389 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
7390 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
7391 int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
7392 if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
7393 amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
7394 I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
7395 CollectAllGarbage("external memory allocation limit reached.");
7396 } else {
7397 *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
7398 }
7399 return *amount_of_external_allocated_memory;
7400}
